sql:
SELECT COUNT(asset_id) AS active_assets_count
FROM digital_assets
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT AVG(file_size) AS average_file_size
FROM asset_versions
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT asset_id, date_created
FROM digital_assets
ORDER BY date_created DESC;

SELECT client_name
FROM client_info
WHERE industry = 'Library';

SELECT COUNT(version_id) AS total_versions
FROM asset_versions
WHERE asset_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
This query assumes that the version history is linear, with each version building upon the previous one; 
The access statistics are aggregated based on the asset ID, providing an overview of how each asset has been accessed and used;
The metadata summary provides insight into the attributes and characteristics of each asset, enabling filtering and sorting based on these attributes.
